Philippe May Become Atlantic Hurricane Soon, Storm Center Says

-- B y   S h e r r y   S u
-- 
2011-10-05T09:51:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/philippe-may-become-atlantic-hurricane-soon-storm-center-says.html
 Tropical Storm Philippe in Atlantic
waters southeast of  Bermuda  is expected to become a hurricane in
the next day or so, the National Hurricane Center said.  The storm, about 580 miles (930 kilometers) from Bermuda,
is moving west-northwest at 6 miles per hour with 65 mph winds,
the Miami-based center said in its latest  advisory . A turn to
the north is forecast for later today as the storm intensifies,
then to the northeast by tomorrow, with no threat to land.  Philippe is the 16th named storm of the  Atlantic hurricane
season  than runs from June through November.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sherry Su in London at 
 lsu23@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Stephen Voss at 
